    • Class org.harctoolbox.ircore.IrSequence

      class IrSequence extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • data
          double[] data
          Duration data, all positive. Even indices are considered flashes, even ones gaps. By definition they are interleaving.

    • Class org.harctoolbox.ircore.IrSignal

      class IrSignal extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • dutyCycle
          Double dutyCycle
          Duty cycle of the modulation. Between 0 and 1. Use null for not assigned.
        • endingSequence
          IrSequence endingSequence
          Ending sequence, sent at the end of transmission. Can be empty, but not null. Actually, most often is empty.
        • frequency
          Double frequency
          Modulation frequency in Hz. Use 0 for not modulated, and null for defaulted.
        • introSequence
          IrSequence introSequence
          Intro sequence, always sent once. Can be empty, but not null.
        • map
          EnumMap<IrSignal.Pass,IrSequence> map
          "Table" for mapping Pass to intro, repeat, or ending sequence.
        • repeatSequence
          IrSequence repeatSequence
          Repeat sequence, sent after the intro sequence if the signal is repeating. Can be empty, but not null.
